<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12206a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12206a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12206a"> 206(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> elle pleura ter / en l&apos;agitant ter</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">(from Chapter XII, <i>Amiti&eacute;</i>, the story <i>Perdre un ami, cest mourir</i>): La petite fille pleura, pleura, pleura et exprima toute <font color="green">[sa]</font> compassion pour les pitoyables orphelins, <font color="green">[tout en]</font> agitant l&apos;eau, l&apos;agitant, l&apos;agitant, l&apos;agitant. <br><font color="green">[The little girl cried, cried, cried and she expressed all of her compassion for the sad orphans, by stirring the water, stirring it, stirring it, stirring it.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 91-2</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: L. <i>ter</i>, three times. </mm> </dd></dl>
